          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 9 1/8 in. by 6 1/2, consisting of 173 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll.1, 2, 5, 33 and 34. The quires, signed with letters, were originally 22 in number, but of the first three only four leaves remain, and ܕand ܗ are altogether lost. Each page has two columns of 36 lines. </p>
